  "prompt": "What should I put on sweet potato fries?",
  "response": "There are plenty of delicious options to enhance sweet potato fries! Here are some popular ideas:\n\n### Seasonings:\n1. **Sea Salt**: Simple and classic.\n2. **Paprika**: Adds a smoky flavor.\n3. **Cinnamon**: For a sweet and savory twist.\n4. **Garlic Powder**: Perfect for a bit of savory kick.\n5. **Chili Powder**: For a spicy touch.\n6. **Cajun Seasoning**: Spicy and flavorful.\n7. **Rosemary**: Earthy and aromatic.\n\n### Sauces and Dips:\n1. **Ketchup**: Classic and tangy.\n2. **Spicy Mayo**: Mix mayo with some sriracha or hot sauce.\n3. **Aioli**: Garlic mayo dip.\n4. **Honey Mustard**: Sweet and tangy.\n5. **BBQ Sauce**: Smoky and sweet.\n6. **Yogurt Dip**: Mix Greek yogurt with herbs.\n7. **Maple Syrup**: Great for a sweet touch.\n\n### Toppings:\n1. **Grated Parmesan Cheese**: Adds a savory depth.\n2. **Crumbled Feta Cheese**: Tangy and creamy.\n3. **Fresh Herbs**: Chives, parsley, or cilantro.\n4. **Bacon Crumbles**: Adds a savory crunch.\n5. **Green Onions**: For a fresh, vibrant garnish.\n\nYou can mix and match these options to suit your taste and create your perfect sweet potato fry experience!",
